THE GAME
--------

  'Xess', pronounced 'ex-sess' or simply 'xess' or whatever way
you want to pronounce its name, even backwards (tsk tsk!). It is a
Workbench game where you have to place 32 coloured 'X' shapes on
an 8 by 8 tile board. The main thing to remember is that a part of
an 'X' shape is placed on a tile you click on and the other part
is on a tile that is at the upper right, lower right, lower left
or upper left, next to the clicked tile.

  Note that 2 'X' shapes can 'cross' each other, as long as both
are of a different colour. Also, any 'X' shape can rotate by
clicking on it. If there is at least one other empty space located
next and diagonally from the clicked position, it will rotate and
the other part of the 'X' shape will go to that space.

  When you complete a game, Xess displays a new board, sometimes
with some 'X' shapes randomly placed...

  Complete the game in the least amount of moves.

  Have fun!

